18:10.840 --> 18:15.380
The late H.B.Piper created in his fiction a race of small, furry, sentient creatures called fuzzies.

18:15.800 --> 18:18.160
These cute aliens proved to be very popular with the fans.

18:18.620 --> 18:24.280
Fuzzy's figured in only two books, Little Fuzzy, and what was later called Fuzzy Sapiens, before Piper died.

18:24.820 --> 18:28.540
But according to Ardeth Mayhar, who recently wrote another installment in the Fuzzy saga entitled

18:28.540 --> 18:32.540
Golden Dream of Fuzzy Odyssey, the fuzzy series did not stop with Piper's death.

18:33.120 --> 18:37.260
Well, Mr. Piper died in 1966.

18:38.860 --> 18:42.000
A suicide, which was a very tragic thing.

18:42.760 --> 18:47.920
And he left a considerable literary estate.

18:48.160 --> 18:51.820
He had been writing rather successfully for a long time.

18:52.860 --> 18:57.040
There was sort of a hiatus there for a number of years

18:57.040 --> 19:01.420
until one of his friends, I believe it was Jerry Purnell, but I'm not certain,

19:02.080 --> 19:05.880
persuaded A's to purchase his literary estate.

19:06.380 --> 19:11.740
All the rights and all of his books and short stories and everything, which they did.

19:13.460 --> 19:23.040
And they reissued Little Fuzzy and Fuzzy Sapiens in a single volume under the fuzzy papers.

19:23.040 --> 19:24.680
And it was very successful.

19:25.340 --> 19:28.900
Had a built-in market of people who remembered the books.

19:29.620 --> 19:32.420
And so they decided that they wanted another book.

19:32.560 --> 19:40.960
So they turned to Mr. William Tuning, who wrote a third book, Fuzzy Bones, which I enjoyed very much.

19:41.260 --> 19:49.420
I based a great deal of the background of my book on the substructure that he had created for their historical background.

19:50.300 --> 19:54.240
After Tuning's effort, May Hart told us, she was asked to write a fuzzy novel.

19:54.560 --> 19:55.580
Here she tells us why.

19:56.600 --> 20:02.180
I believe it was Susan Allison, who was then the head science fiction editor at A's,

20:03.000 --> 20:06.660
decided that they wanted a book from the viewpoint of the little aliens.

20:08.020 --> 20:19.760
Well, my editor had just bought paperback rights to my first two double-day books.

20:19.820 --> 20:24.480
And she was in the process of putting them into production for A's.

20:24.900 --> 20:29.640
And she had had a great deal of back and forth conversation with my agent,

20:29.660 --> 20:33.480
who is still black staggered at how fast I am.

20:34.220 --> 20:38.880
And so one day the phone rang, that dear phone, it was Susan Allison.

20:39.760 --> 20:46.680
She said, would you be interested in writing a book to continue H. Bean Piper's fuzzy series?

20:46.820 --> 20:47.780
Are you familiar with mine?

20:47.960 --> 20:49.460
I said, yes, I've got my teeth on them.

20:49.840 --> 20:51.380
And she said, well, would you be interested?

20:51.740 --> 20:53.960
We want one from the viewpoint of the aliens.

20:54.800 --> 21:00.360
And she said, I shouldn't say this, but we were kicking it around the office

21:00.360 --> 21:03.560
and trying to figure who was extremely fast and partly alien.

21:03.740 --> 21:04.900
And naturally we thought of you.

21:05.680 --> 21:09.960
Well, I was flat, you know, because I am both.

21:12.600 --> 21:15.600
So I said, well, I'll tell you what, I will reread the books.

21:16.740 --> 21:24.420
And then I will write whatever feels comfortable so that I know how well I fit into a fuzzy skin.

21:24.420 --> 21:28.080
And you will be able to tell how well you like what I do.

21:28.700 --> 21:30.080
And then we'll go from there.

21:30.800 --> 21:34.100
To write about fuzzies, may her found it necessary to put herself in their place.

21:34.580 --> 21:35.880
This was in early February.

21:37.060 --> 21:42.380
So I sat down and it's a very funny thing.

21:42.560 --> 21:48.580
Becoming an alien is not all that difficult, but you have to have been a very peculiar child.

21:48.840 --> 21:50.880
You'll be able to do it well.

21:52.000 --> 21:54.980
So I remembered when I was two feet tall.

21:55.100 --> 21:57.500
I can remember back before I was two years old.

21:58.000 --> 22:02.220
I remembered how the world is full of shoes and kneecaps.

22:03.400 --> 22:05.720
You know, everything is tremendous.

22:06.140 --> 22:10.140
Shrubs or trees and trees are just something up there like clouds, you know.

22:10.500 --> 22:19.260
So I shrunk myself down to two feet tall and put myself on a world where everything thought I was delicious.

22:20.640 --> 22:22.000
And went from there.

